reviews_data.review_text: Both pasta dishes looked great at first sight. Once we started to mix up the pasta it were a lot of excessive oil. The veal meatballs were ok.

Appetiser asparagus ends inedible, swimming in an excessive melted parmesan pool (not 'shavings'), and I did something I've never before done in 50-plus yrs of travel: I off-loaded the retrievable veg onto my side plate & asked that all the melted cheese & the fibrous bits of inedible asparagus - with explanation - be returned to the kitchen.

My pasta cooked correctly al dente, but my dining partner's gnocchi drowned in tomato sauce, to the point where it resembled a soupy stew, not any sort of recognizable Italian dish.

Just to round it off, dessert panna cotta tasted (& textured?) as though made with tinned evaporated milk, not fresh cream/milk.

Altogether a most disappointing meal, especially because (it used to be) one of our business's favourite places to bring clients.
Not any more.
😢

reviews_data.review_text: Average food for an Italian, and just unfriendly service from the ‘unwelcome’ at the door to the miserable waitress.
The place has an amazing atmosphere. The service is amazing and the food was terrific! If you are ever in cape town you have to try out this restaurant!
Very good menu. Good portions. Relaxed atmosphere.

The servers, waiter, and staff were excellent. One of our dishes was not done correctly, and we reported it to the restaurant owner in a friendly supportive manner. What a disappointment this man was, getting personal and aggressive with us. He is a pathetic person who treats his customers and staff like kids.

Do not confuse this place with the excellent restaurant of the same name in Johannesburg as the one in Johannesburg personally for me is one of the best restaurants in the world. The owner of the Johannesburg branch is a kind and friendly man always looking after me and my friends and family and I am a regular.

I had a great time in this quaint restaurant. My four  stars go to cosy ambiance, professional waiters and management.  The seafood pasta I had, was dull and forgettable.

Food was fantastic - steak, pasta, salads, and desserts all delicious.  Owner even came over and was very gracious.  Recommended to us by a friend and we would highly recommend it as well.
Good carbonara and tortellini. Taste was good, price was ok but a little more pricey than I thought it would be. Service was a little slow. All in all a good Italian place with nice atmosphere.

I ĥave been to many Italian restaurants in my life. In Bologna, Venice, Florence even a super fancy one in London. Il Leone's food is superior to practically all of them. The Cacio e Pepe, Peasano and Carbonara pastas had the most moreish and perfectly balanced sauces I've ever tasted.  The salads are well balanced and not overpowered by fancy dressings. The Tiramisu is light and not over sweet. If you're in Cape Town and you're craving Italian food please do yourself a favour and eat here. Oh and no 10% bully enforced tip at lunch in late October 2025.

reviews_data.review_text: Ordered their chicken penne for the first time on UberEats and it is DELISH! Homey and comforting. The chicken has a nice grilled flavour to it and the sauce is wonderfully flavoured. I have eaten at the actually Il Leone restaurant a few times, and am a sucker for their carbonara and the gnocchi with 4 cheese sauce. Really tasty pastas! The atmosphere of the restaurant also has a wonderful atmosphere - cozy and welcoming.
It is not an italian restaurant anymore and changed the name.

Amazing Italian restaurant, great pastas, good quantity of food per dish and not super crazy prices. They served us bread  and thyme crackers on the house and that was just tooo good, we ordered for one more basket. Being vegetarian, I asked for more veggies in a Penne Aurora pasta and they did a fantastic job. Very friendly and welcoming service as well. My friend was very happy with the generous portion of food. Many wine bottle options, but 'by glass' is few. Good restaurant for a conversation.

Found this on Google and made a reservation via email, for our wedding anniversary as we were on vacation. Coincidentally found out that it was also one of the recommended restaurants in the hood, by our accommodation hosts.

The restaurant is rather lovely with many art pieces, but if I’d to nitpick, it’d be the proximity of the tables. Servers tend to have to squeeze between tables and my chair was cornered at a pillar (which they’d offer to change the position, but I’d be almost next to another diner, so I declined). This also meant it gets uncomfortable if your neighbours were loud.

Food wise, we’d the ceviche, mussels in white wine, burrata for starters and grilled chicken and queen prawns for mains. Mussels had a slight stench and chicken less salty, but the rest were delicious, especially the prawns.

Service was immaculate nonetheless, which really made our night(: Shoutout to our wonderful waitress Indya, easily the best service I’ve had since arriving in Cape Town.
2 food poisonings

THIS PLACE IMPOSES A 10% MANDATORY TIP WITHOUT TELLING YOU UPFRONT AND BULLIES TOURISTS

The above speaks for itself. We rounded up the bill which practically provided for a 7% tip and the waitress took a look at the receipt with our written tip amount, threw it away and then printed a new receipt for us and told us a 10% tip on top of the meal price plus VAT is mandatory. It is not stated anywhere in the menu that we had to tip this amount and it’s not a lot of money but the way it was delivered was extremely rude. The waitress who dealt with us also kept harassing us and saying passive aggressive things like “can you calculate 10% without a calculator?”. I can’t help but to feel that we were targeted for being tourists and bullied.

Anyway, the food was mid and overpriced. The pasta was not al dente, the meat dishes were overcooked / chewy.

The restaurant also tries to upsell water to its customers. We were not told the price and were served 2 bottles of 750ml water (which costs ~7€/140ZAR in total). We would expect that the price of something that costs 50% of a pasta/main dish would be told to customers.

You can find much better food and better service elsewhere.

IL Leone is absolutely exceptional. It's not cheap per se but the quality of the food, the venue, the service and the kindness within the system.

It's brilliant.

If you can afford to treat yourself with a meal at IL Leone, trust your gut, order what you desire every now and then. It's bloody brilliant.

I want to go back.
I had one of the best Pastas I've ever had!!! Wow

Always a pleasure to dine at Il Leone. Beautiful dining experience with very good solid flavour in their dishes in a warm atmosphere.

Good wine selection on the international side. Unfortunately not that big of a selection of South African wines.
If you’re looking for great Italian cuisine and great service, I’ll Leone is the place. Coming there for many years and it’s always super!!

The food was excellent aswell as the service.

We sat outside and unfortunately due to construction on the property next door it got quite loud at times but that did not dampen the mood.

Since we were celebrating a birthday they brought out a complementary birthday plate. Overall a great experience and I would definitely recommend this restaurant to a friend.
Excellent food , great vibe

I was quite excited to finally dine at this establishment.
Food: a great menu selection across different proteins and vegetables. However, all 6 of our dishes just lacked salt. We had to add salt, pepper, chilli and garlic in order to bring some life to the dish.
Service: decent service and friendly staff, kept trying to up sell, but we stood strong lol.
Atmosphere: warm, welcoming and comfortable.
Il Leone has been around for many years and Daniel keeps up the great vibe and food year in year out. A great commitment to his trade .

Including menu ‘cause it’s absolutely impossible to find otherwise. Bolognese and carbonara were decent, pasta slightly softer than ideal but good flavour.

Edit. If you saw that photo of my friend no you didn’t 😌
One of the best food experiences

One of the best pasta. The quality is amazing and prices within expectation. About 200rand for a pasta and for this quality, worth the money. The tomato sauce blend in nicely with the fragrance of seafood. Pasta was al dente. It would easily beat many pasta dishes i tried in rome, ischia and napoli. Top 5 best pasta ever.

reviews_data.review_text:
I enjoy this restaurant consistently good, clean good staff been going here for 10+years, normally fully booked winters-
day today normally not this empty, book in advance…

When Il Leone first opened it was sensational. Over the years it has deteriorated. We haven’t been for a while but tried it again as we were told it had improved. It hasn’t. It’s overpriced and the food is average. The service I can’t fault. But paying over R400 for a plate of meh pasta and a bottle of average wine for over R1000, it’s simply not worth it. I’m not price sensitive. I just don’t understand why they’ve priced themselves like this with no comparable offering! Maybe it’s for tourists. As a local, I would stay away.

Lovely selection of Italian dishes and wines. We opted for two seafood pastas, which were both delicious and really decent serving sizes. The service was amazing, the drinks were good, and atmosphere was warm and comfortable.

Overall experience is great. The only disappoint part was steak, don’t ever eat steak here, it is too salty. I don’t think they will replace u a new one as well. If u come here’s try risotto. I give 5/5 on risotto
My clients love this restaurant

We had a great dinner at Il Leone Mastrantonio and really enjoyed the variety of dishes. The pasta was fresh and flavorful, the seafood risotto was rich and satisfying, and the steak was perfectly cooked.

For dessert, we had the panna cotta and tiramisu,both were beautifully presented and delicious. The atmosphere is cozy yet elegant, and the service was warm and attentive. It is a lovely place for a relaxed.

The upstairs dining area is well laid out for social distancing- but the minimalist look creates an echo that makes for very noisy dining.

Pasta was delicious but I have to be honest R176 for vegetarian sage butter  Ravioli......mmm I'm not sure about.
Trust, our waiter was excellent.
Great food. Great atmosphere. Great service. I’m not a fan of Italian food but these guys are phenomenal!!

A personal favourite for Italian food; consistently delicious pasta with fresh ingredients and great flavours. The pasta itself is always perfectly cooked and the dishes are expertly seasoned. Pictured is one of their ravioli dishes; which like many others was scrumptious and unexpectedly filling. Though the pasta's are a must have they also have great steaks and other main dishes and the desserts are awesome. Very popular so would advise booking in advance for larger groups. Staff are always friendly and the atmosphere is relaxed and cozy.
Great dinner
Amazing venue, great quality food, great service. Best prices

Been twice both times, service  and food amazing.

Authentic Italian style

Fair prices

Tops

I visited Il Leone on the 29th of March for the 3rd or 4th time because I know the food is absolutely amazing. However , this time upon arrival we were treated so poorly by the hostess. She was extremely rude , she rushed us to our table and insisted that we order in the next 5 minutes before the kitchen closes. As we place our order , we see her loudly and excitingly welcoming two new tables, who both placed orders 30 minutes after us in no rush at all. I am extremely disappointed in this because this was becoming one of my favourite restaurants. I felt discriminated against and it spoiled my whole dinner.
Great food though.
Fantastisch lekker eten. Prachtige setting en heel vriendelijk personeel. Topadres! De beste risotto die ik in lange tijd gegeten heb.
Always good food and great service

Fantastic, the food is absolutely phenomenal. I had the tortellini, oh my word the cream sauce was amazing and complimented the tortellini so so well. Your taste buds will thank you and sing your praises afterward. I indulged in the Tiramisu as well, it was so flavorsome, everything you want it to be, if we didn't leave I would have had more.

We booked a table for 8pm and by 8:45pm still had not been seated. We were not looked after, no-one offered to take our order for starters in the meantime or offered us a snack. We stood waiting for 45 mins and kept getting told the table was nearly ready and was being prepped. When I asked if we could go to the table in the meantime they admitted there were still people there who would not leave. We left after that, most annoyed. It could have been handled much better by management. We will not go there again despite being patrons for years. The next day we called and the owner (manager?) said we were lying. We are not impressed at all!
So great to visit this place after a few years. Stil as amazing and even better. Talent looked after us and our whole table gave food and service a full 10 out of 10. Most memorable dining experience

I had one of the best steaks at this restaurant. The pasta was also great. Its close to the V&A Waterfront. The restaurant is spacious, decorated with art and the food is superb. I recommend this place if you like Italian.
Food poisoning of 3 people! Be careful
We are big fans of Illovo Mastrantonio and Il Leone was equally superb. We had a lovely meal, starters to share (a delicious Cesar salad and fried white bait!). We'll definitely be back

I stumbled onto this Italian spot by chance. There was a warm welcome and a buzz about the place even before dinner time. Service was excellent. The wine selection really good and well priced. The complimentary bread and flat bread, a good start. The langoustine pasta was perfect - pasta was al dente, the chili was just enough and the langoustine tails and pieces were tasty.  I liked the art on the walls, some of which you can purchase. Will be back one day. Maybe for a first date 😁

A lovely find. Oodles of atmosphere and clearly loved by local CT residents. The food was very good without much finesse and the friendly service was as slow as the arrival of our food. Will definitely go back and we'll be happy to adjust star ratings if deserved. Have been back several times since writing the above and very happy to give full star ratings as the welcome and service alone deserve them. The food is very good and is presented in a simple manner and just tastes good. Lovely people.

Booked a table for 8pm. We were shown to the bar at 8pm while "the people at our table paid up and they were busy resetting the table". We ordered drinks. We stood. We were ignored. At 8:20pm we enquired as to when we would be able to sit down. We were again told "the people at the table had lingered and they had just finished paying and right now they were busy setting the table". We stood some more. We waited. We ordered more drinks.

Finally at 8:45pm we lost our patience. We started moving up the stairs to go and sit down "while they set our table". We were blocked from going upstairs to this imaginary table and at that stage we left.

No one communicated with us until we enquired about our table (several times), no one offered us drinks, no one gave us a menu to peruse while we waited, no one offered to put snacks on the bar while we waited for our table. Nothing.

To put the icing on the cake, after I got hold of the owners number and communicated with him, I was told that I was lying, that it was only 20-25 minutes that we waited and that I could have a nice bottle of wine when I came back...
Great food! Service was slow at first but improved greatly!

reviews_data.review_text: Good Italian food😋, the only thing is that if you eat inside the restaurant there is too much noise🤫, it is better outside 😊 At the entrance they have sanitizer, a mask is needed when entering and the temperature they test you 😉

I come to this place every Thursday for Lunch. The staff are very friendly and Talent was our server and he’s excellent and the dishes I enjoy are the spaghetti bolognese which is the best I have ever had and also their cream sauce penne chicken pasta with mushrooms. Overall love this place but only order the spaghetti bolognese because it is the best.
Situated in an amazing area. The ambiance is amazing 🤩 wooden floors and great hosts. Meatballs and pasta that melts into your mouth.

Would definitely recommend this place if you enjoy Italian food - the food, service and general restaurant atmosphere are all great.  There are one or two minor things that could "polish" the experience more, such as decent olive oil with the starter / bread ... but no deal-breakers.
Linefish was great!
Best Italian restaurant in cape town
The food and service was great, but the vibe is rather loud so possible but not so easy to hold intimate conversation, especially for octogenarians.

Visited ILM for a special occasion. The food was good but it was incredibly noisy. The waitron never enquired whether we wanted water but just kept pouring water, which we assumed was included in the service . . . until we received the bill! The water is marked-up at least 400% from what the restaurant probably pays for it. Demanding payment for an item that was not requested is downright unethical! It ruined the evening & I won't return.
Good food and very good service from Tafadzwa.

Sadly Il leone (being an absolute favourite restaurants for the last 4 years) has definitely gone down hill.

I phoned to make a booking and offered to spell my name (as most places usually get it wrong, I was told by the not so friendly lady, “I know how to spell!” ~ Quite rude and very awkward but I let it go...

Few weeks after, I phoned and made a booking with another lady for this past Thursday for 8 of us, most of whom haven’t been and my husband and I have been raving about the food for quite some time. The woman I spoke to took my name (I didn’t dare offer to spell it again!), surname and she also took my cellphone nr and all was confirmed on the phone - I made 100% sure and she read all details back to me.

We got to the restaurant and what do you know... NOT a trace of a booking and the not so lovely male owner was unbelievably rude and didn’t offer to rectify one of his staff’s mistakes nor apologise and we got placed outside in the cold and he was never at our table again...very embarrassing to say the least.

I am extremely saddened and shocked by the RUDE service (or lack thereof) received! Our waitresses was amazing but management / ownership needs some hospitality training!

Amazing! The ambiance and setting of the restaurant is a cozy, upscape space with a sprinkle of art gallery but in your dining room sort of a feel. The staff was wonderful and so friendly! And saving the best for last the food! Oh boy was it delicious, especially that four cheese sauce that was on the raviolis. I would come back just for that incredible sauce wow!
Exquisite food, definitely worth a visit again!
Excellent food, the service was top notch. We will be back
Great food and good service. A nice atmosphere in the restaurant.  Will go again.

Absolutely fantastic!!
We had a business lunch and it was perfect.
The staff were really helpful and with great welcoming spirit.

reviews_data.review_text: Very enjoyable meal
Waited over an hour for our main course.

I visited il leone two times in one week and the food is ok but the service needs a lot more to improve. Both times they over charge bottled water (more bottles than delivered on the bill) Very long waiting time for food and it feels like visiting “Fawlty Towers”

After seeing the numerous good reviews i decided to go to get dinner with my significant other. we booked a reservation. Upon arrival we were directed to a table and waited for service around 10 mins. And only saw the waiter twice during out whole stay.We ordered a risotto al funghi (R255) and a ragu pasta (R180) the food was bland and tasted like something you can get at a local bistro at about half the price. After this we asked for the bill and our waiter scoffed at me tipping R50. Overall it was quite a dissapointing experience and definently left us feeling as if the evening was wasted.

Classic Italian dining experience
Great cocktails too!
Zeer aangenaam restaurant. Vrij druk met de lunch. Vriendelijk personeel, leuke kaart, goede wijnkaart. Zeer betaalbaar. Klein terrasje buiten, maar binnen prima en leuke sfeer.

Absolutely appalling service.. waited an hour and half for food, arrogant manager and rude waiter. Then to top it all off we were berated by manager and waiter for not paying the full service charge.. What "service".. ?? Steer clear of this.. overrated and half baked.
Very friendly staff + very delicious food, would recommend 100 %!
Great service and atmosphere with good selection of Italian food (seafood tagliatelle is a must) and South African wine. Better to book for lunch, as it may get a bit busy.

Best Gnocchi in Cape Town, you will not find anything better elsewhere. Portion is not so big but so worth it! I will highly recommend this place. Thanks guys, you have never disappointed on Gnocchi. Will keep returning  and ordering💛💛💛

Terrific white tablecloth experience. We were able to snag a last-second reservation thanks to a cancelation and are so grateful we did. Caprese was good but the olive oil was great. I had the lamb chops: juicy and delicious. Wife had line fish and it was flakey, flavorful, and perfectly prepared. We especially liked the side of greens served with each dish. Can’t say enough about the ambiance here: it feels both fancy and casual at the same time. Service was friendly if just a little slow.

⭐ Rating: 1/5

I'm writing both as a concerned fellow vegan and in support of a friend who recently dined at Il Leone for a family celebration. The experience, as recounted to me, raises some important issues about how vegan customers are catered to and treated.

My friend, choosing a recommended vegan option, was let down by both the lack of understanding of the food served to her (which was not vegan) and the staff's response to the feedback. The reaction was passive-aggressive, and the alternative vegan dish provided was equally unsatisfactory. The hostess's visible irritation at my friend's lack of enthusiasm further added to the discomfort of the evening.

As a vegan, I understand the challenges of finding vegan meal options and worse, being given non-vegan food under the pretense of it being vegan.

I am hopeful that this feedback will be taken constructively. There is a growing vegan community in Cape Town, and we look forward to dining at establishments that not only offer diverse vegan options but also extend courtesy and understanding to their customers. Il Leone has the potential to be such a place if it chooses to embrace these values.

How dismal my family celebration turned out last night. I left without having eaten. No fault of our lovely waitress who tried her best. I am a vegan. The options were limited and I went with the waitress’s recommendation - risotto. It tasted like plastic. I complained. The hostess was very passive aggressive and suggested I order something else. I then approached her while she was complaining about me. Everyone was eating dessert when my replacement arrived. Raw zucchini and salty tomato water. I asked someone else to taste it for me as well because it was inedible. I sent it back. Then the hostess was upset when I wasn’t grateful to get a free sorbet. This was a shocking experience.
High quality Italian food, so simple dishes with so much care put into every dish and ingredient. Very cool and clean aesthetic. We always come back.

My experience at this Italian restaurant was amazing from start to finish. They responded to my email promptly and positively, and we got a reservation right away. When we arrived, we were greeted warmly and personally. As a passionate home cook, winner of a TV cooking show, and someone with Italian roots, I hold Italian cuisine to very high standards. I have to say—this was the best Italian food I’ve ever had outside of Italy. The dishes were wonderfully seasoned, and neither of us had to add a single thing. The service was impeccable.

We can’t wait to return and will absolutely recommend this place to our friends and family.
